  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because if it there was 100%, the offices would never exist, would never tick.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So it was always done with some sort of-- of-- combinations of interactions between one office and another, and what-- whatever it is.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And if you were the accountant, and one of my brothers was the accountant that-- in that enterprise, you would have been the one who's sent to jail for-- for any-- for any abnormalities that were.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And if you couldn't trade these things to keep the wheels running, then you would be kicked out and you had no income [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Liberated in the-- in the true sense of the word, the technical sense of liberation, does not apply to me in that sense, because nobody came into our camp to-- to open the door and say, you are free.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I was liberated-- inverted commas-- the day of the Japanese surrender, in August '45.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember that day very clearly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember it because when the news came through that the Japanese-- Japanese surrendered, and we knew that it's coming because we could see the-- the attacks on Shanghai wharfs and so on, that the Americans were-- and we knew what's happening, and so on.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That day, suddenly the-- the-- the self-- self-confident occupiers suddenly tried to melt into thin air.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They walked the street hugging the-- the walls of the buildings, trying not to be noticed, trying not to be seen.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a picture to be seen and to be-- observe to see what happens over-- withing hours, in the mentality of a people from being the-- the process of force and power and suddenly to become the subject of mercy and-- and-- and and the-- and the potential-- and the potential subject of accountability.",
      "word_count": 55
    }
  ],
